WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:16.391 --> 00:18.441
[newscaster] <i>You're watching</i>
<i>Channel 38, Austin.</i>

00:18.519 --> 00:20.309
<i>Building a better Texas.</i>

00:20.395 --> 00:25.525
<i>Now, from your 24-hour news service,</i>
<i>this is</i> Good Morning Austin.

00:25.609 --> 00:29.149
<i>People in the Southwest are looking
for relief from a deadly heat wave.</i>

00:29.237 --> 00:33.527
<i>A few areas, like Fort Worth, Texas,
and parts of Oklahoma, saw rain Monday</i>

00:33.617 --> 00:35.287
<i>for the first time in a long time.</i>

00:35.368 --> 00:38.498
<i>But for most,
the month-long drought continues.</i>

00:38.581 --> 00:40.621
<i>- NBC's Cummins reports.</i>
- [dog barking]

00:42.125 --> 00:43.245
[flies buzzing]

00:43.335 --> 00:45.665
[dog barking and growling]

00:55.138 --> 00:56.678
[phone ringing]

00:57.265 --> 00:58.845
[coffee percolating]

01:00.185 --> 01:02.185
[ringing continues]

01:10.571 --> 01:12.674
[Robin on recording]
<i>You've reached the Murray O'Hairs.</i>

01:12.698 --> 01:15.078
<i>- Leave a message.</i>
- [answering machine beeps]

01:15.158 --> 01:18.788
[Luke] <i>Hey, it's Luke.</i>
<i>It's, uh, 10:00. Where are you?</i>

01:18.871 --> 01:20.251
<i>Everyone's here.</i>

01:22.082 --> 01:23.832
[answering machine clicks]

01:30.507 --> 01:32.337
- [door opens]
- [dogs barking]

01:33.593 --> 01:36.853
Hey, y'all.
Gonna be a scorcher today.

01:36.930 --> 01:37.930
Phew!

01:53.405 --> 01:55.695
[Robin] Where are we?
[Madalyn] I don't know.

01:55.783 --> 01:57.703
[Garth grunts]

01:57.785 --> 01:58.785
[Robin] Grandma?

01:59.787 --> 02:02.827
[Madalyn] It's all right, Red.
We're gonna get out of this.

02:02.915 --> 02:05.285
- Garth?
- [Garth] Yes, Mother.

02:05.375 --> 02:07.495
Did you get a good look at anybody?
Recognize anyone?

02:07.585 --> 02:09.835
- [Garth] No, Mother.
- [Madalyn sighs]

02:09.922 --> 02:11.802
[Robin] Shh.
I think someone's coming.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.804
Check their restraints.

02:15.886 --> 02:17.822
[Madalyn] You wanna tell us
what the hell we're doin' here?

02:17.846 --> 02:18.846
[man] Shut up.

02:18.931 --> 02:20.158
[Madalyn] You're tellin' me to shut up?

02:20.182 --> 02:23.062
I don't think you know whose weeds
you're pissing in, buddy.

02:23.143 --> 02:24.537
- I said shut up.
- [Madalyn] I heard you.

02:24.561 --> 02:26.561
I chose to ignore you.

02:26.647 --> 02:28.397
Who are you working for, huh?

02:28.481 --> 02:32.491
Did Jerry Falwell put you up to this, huh?
The Baptists, that it?

02:32.569 --> 02:34.588
- [Garth whispers] Mother, please.
- I think we're good.

02:34.612 --> 02:36.202
All right, let's go.

02:36.281 --> 02:39.241
[Madalyn] Cocksuckers,
you're not gonna get away with this!

02:41.787 --> 02:44.077
[shouting] Don't you know who I am?

02:49.627 --> 02:51.497
[softly] God damn it.

02:51.588 --> 02:54.218
- [dogs barking]
- [indistinct radio chatter]

02:57.219 --> 02:59.389
So, Mr. Collier,
you say the cars are gone now.

02:59.471 --> 03:00.573
Shouldn't they just be in them?

03:00.597 --> 03:03.177
[Roy] The door was open,
breakfast on the table,

03:03.266 --> 03:05.586
- and they'd never leave without the dogs.
- [man] Mmm-hmm.

03:06.770 --> 03:09.940
And you say that this lady lives here
with her son and his daughter?

03:10.023 --> 03:13.653
Yes. Uh, no.
The granddaughter's from her other son.

03:14.820 --> 03:16.820
It's an interesting living arrangement.

03:18.323 --> 03:19.533
Wait a minute.

03:19.616 --> 03:22.156
Madalyn Murray O'Hair.
That's who we're talking about here?

03:24.121 --> 03:27.371
Are you sure that this isn't just another
one of her publicity stunts?

03:28.583 --> 03:31.173
Aren't you even gonna take
any fingerprints, sir?

03:33.171 --> 03:36.011
[smacks lips] Mr. Collier, this is Texas.

03:37.175 --> 03:39.255
Not against the law to go missing here.

03:41.972 --> 03:43.532
[Madalyn] Garth, I loosened it.
I loosened it.

03:43.556 --> 03:45.451
Come here. Give me your hands.
Give me your hands.

03:45.475 --> 03:46.870
- [Garth] What are you...
- Give me your hands.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.524
Just get it untied. That's...

03:48.603 --> 03:50.164
[Garth] I... I can't.
[Madalyn] You can do it.

03:50.188 --> 03:52.375
- [Garth] Oh, my God. It's really...
- That's it. That's it.

03:52.399 --> 03:53.710
[Garth] What kind of knot is that?

03:53.734 --> 03:55.404
[Madalyn] Come on.
You can do it.

03:55.485 --> 03:57.315
[Garth] Well, get closer to me, then.

03:57.404 --> 03:59.084
- [Madalyn] Oh, all right.
- [Garth grunts]

03:59.114 --> 04:00.454
[Garth] Jesus!
[Madalyn] Come on.

04:00.532 --> 04:01.952
[Garth] Oh. Almost.
I almost got...

04:02.034 --> 04:04.294
[Madalyn] Come on.
[Garth pants] No, I... No, it's not...

04:04.369 --> 04:06.806
- It's useless. It's not gonna happen.
- Jesus, Mary and Joseph!

04:06.830 --> 04:09.460
I knew I should have sent you
to fucking Boy Scouts.

04:09.541 --> 04:11.310
[Garth] I don't know what you think
you're gonna do anyway.

04:11.334 --> 04:12.344
They both have guns.

04:12.419 --> 04:14.629
[Madalyn sighs]
If we could get these hoods off,

04:14.712 --> 04:17.382
we might have a better idea
of what we're dealing with.

04:17.464 --> 04:18.505
[Garth grunts]

04:18.591 --> 04:20.011
- Come on. Try again.
- [Garth] No.

04:20.093 --> 04:21.821
- [Madalyn] Come on, Garthy...
- No, stop it.

04:21.845 --> 04:23.715
[Madalyn] Don't you disobey your mother!

04:23.806 --> 04:25.574
[Garth] Or what, you're gonna
take me over your knee?

04:25.598 --> 04:27.827
[Madalyn] Yes, I just might...
[Robin] Stop it, both of you!

04:27.851 --> 04:29.481
[Madalyn sighing]

04:31.980 --> 04:34.650
[Madalyn softly]
God damn it, I have to pee.

04:34.732 --> 04:35.982
Hey, people!

04:36.068 --> 04:40.658
If you don't let me out of here,
I'm gonna piss all over your floor!

04:45.577 --> 04:48.037
[sighs] Lady, you're gonna
need to calm down.

04:48.121 --> 04:51.251
[Madalyn] Calm down?
You want me to calm down, shit for brains?

04:51.333 --> 04:53.561
In case you hadn't noticed,
we've got bags over our heads,

04:53.585 --> 04:56.545
we're all tied up and I gotta pee!

04:56.629 --> 04:59.969
You do what we say and everyone
gets out of here safe and sound.

05:00.050 --> 05:02.470
[Madalyn] Oh, now that sounds
like the big man in charge.

05:02.552 --> 05:04.012
Is that the big man in charge?

05:04.096 --> 05:07.056
Get this goddamn thing off of my head
and show me who you are.

05:07.140 --> 05:09.480
You think you got
the balls to take me on?

05:09.559 --> 05:10.599
[softly] Jesus Christ.

05:11.603 --> 05:13.523
[Madalyn] What?
What's going on?

05:14.606 --> 05:16.206
- Garth, what's going on?
- [Garth sighs]

05:16.274 --> 05:18.154
- Oh, my God.
- Robin.

05:18.235 --> 05:20.235
[Madalyn] Oh, my God,
is that who I think it is?

05:21.488 --> 05:22.698
Fuck.

05:22.780 --> 05:24.070
[sighs]

05:29.371 --> 05:30.831
Hello, Madalyn.

05:31.915 --> 05:34.455
- [line ringing]
- [indistinct chatter]

05:36.419 --> 05:40.049
- [Bill] <i>This is Bill Murray.</i>
- Bill, it's Roy. Roy Collier.

05:40.132 --> 05:41.172
What do you want?

05:42.092 --> 05:44.302
<i>It's your mom... and Robin and Garth.</i>

05:45.220 --> 05:46.390
<i>They've disappeared.</i>

05:47.305 --> 05:48.595
I just saw them in Dallas.

05:48.681 --> 05:49.721
<i>I'm not kidding.</i>

05:49.807 --> 05:52.977
<i>The police said that in order for somebody
to officially be considered missing,</i>

05:53.061 --> 05:55.941
<i>they need somebody in the family
to file a report.</i>

05:56.023 --> 05:57.363
Why would I do that?

05:57.440 --> 06:00.360
Besides, they're probably off
on some crazy trip again.

06:00.443 --> 06:02.703
<i>- No, this is different, Bill.</i>
- Roy...

06:02.779 --> 06:04.859
you know they're not in my life anymore.

06:04.948 --> 06:07.408
And, frankly,
I'd like to keep it that way.

06:07.492 --> 06:08.542
Okay?

06:08.618 --> 06:09.828
<i>Bill...</i>

06:24.801 --> 06:25.931
Ferguson...

06:26.594 --> 06:29.394
I need those 600 words
on the Alamo anniversary by 5:00.

06:29.472 --> 06:33.522
Relax, man. It's the same story I wrote
last year and the year before that.

06:33.601 --> 06:35.914
Well, can't help it
if nothing ever happens in San Antonio.

06:35.938 --> 06:39.478
No, plenty happens in San Antonio.
I just don't get to write about it.

06:39.566 --> 06:41.816
- Where you going?
- [phone ringing]

06:42.735 --> 06:44.315
[sighs] Shit.

06:47.032 --> 06:49.742
- Jack Ferguson.
- [Roy] <i>This is the reporter?</i>

06:49.826 --> 06:51.076
On a good day.

06:51.161 --> 06:54.501
<i>You know Madalyn Murray O'Hair?
She's disappeared.</i>

06:54.581 --> 06:55.831
Madalyn Murray O'Hair?

06:55.915 --> 06:57.825
<i>The damn cops won't do anything.</i>

06:57.917 --> 07:00.337
<i>Only thing I could think to do
was call a reporter.</i>

07:00.420 --> 07:02.710
- Who's this?
<i>- Name's Roy. But I gotta go.</i>

07:02.797 --> 07:06.297
<i>If you wanna know more,
come by 1682 Greystone Drive tonight.</i>

07:06.384 --> 07:08.014
- What...
<i>- I'll be there.</i>

07:08.095 --> 07:09.465
- [dial tone]
- Hello?

07:37.749 --> 07:39.919
[gospel music playing faintly on radio]

07:40.002 --> 07:41.132
[Pup] Madalyn?

07:42.879 --> 07:45.719
Bless this food to our use...

07:45.798 --> 07:47.378
and us to thy service.

07:47.467 --> 07:48.797
- Amen.
- [Mrs. Murray] Amen.

07:50.095 --> 07:53.215
Now, I don't suppose
you found a job today?

07:53.306 --> 07:54.466
[Madalyn] I had an interview.

07:54.975 --> 07:57.885
But I didn't get a law degree
to be a damn receptionist.

07:57.978 --> 08:01.358
[chuckles] You'd be lucky
to be someone's receptionist.

08:01.439 --> 08:03.109
If I were you, I'd start praying.

08:03.191 --> 08:04.731
How do you put up with him, Mother?

08:04.817 --> 08:07.277
The question is, how do I tolerate you?

08:08.196 --> 08:10.116
Living here for free.

08:10.198 --> 08:12.078
- Bringing a bastard into my house.
- Pup!

08:12.617 --> 08:14.787
Don't you ever call my son that.

08:15.870 --> 08:20.250
Sweetie, why don't you just take
your dinner and go on to our room? Hmm?

08:21.334 --> 08:22.884
[Pup] I am sorry, Billy Boy.

08:22.960 --> 08:25.710
I was just trying to make a point
about your momma, huh?

08:31.178 --> 08:33.217
I've got a point I'd like to make.

08:33.304 --> 08:34.345
What else is new?

08:34.431 --> 08:36.471
No, this is important.

08:36.558 --> 08:37.928
Got an announcement.

08:38.893 --> 08:40.602
Getting another grandchild.

08:41.688 --> 08:44.478
That's right. Your precious daughter's
got herself knocked up again.

08:44.566 --> 08:46.026
- Oh, honey, no.
- Yeah.

08:46.109 --> 08:48.989
And the guy's kicked me to the curb again,
saying it's not his,

08:49.071 --> 08:52.661
when I know for a fact
it absolutely is his.

08:52.740 --> 08:53.950
You're an embarrassment.

08:54.701 --> 08:56.911
That's right.
That's right.

08:56.994 --> 08:58.124
Walk away.

08:59.289 --> 09:00.539
Just like they did.

09:01.708 --> 09:03.708
[door opens and slams]

09:08.256 --> 09:09.296
[sighs]

09:09.382 --> 09:10.842
I'm sorry, Mother.

09:10.925 --> 09:15.675
- You wanna tell me what happened?
- I don't know. Condom broke?

09:15.763 --> 09:17.313
You sure you wanna keep it?

09:18.225 --> 09:21.885
I mean, I can take care of Pup,
and you know how he loves little Bill,

09:21.978 --> 09:24.308
and hopefully he'll come around.

09:24.397 --> 09:25.517
He's right.

09:26.691 --> 09:29.531
I got a law degree and no job,
and a kid and no husband.

09:29.611 --> 09:32.661
The only thing I do have is judgment.
I get plenty of that.

09:32.739 --> 09:35.529
Maddy, you made a couple of mistakes,
that's all.

09:35.617 --> 09:39.327
You know, I see these housewives
in their identical homes

09:39.412 --> 09:41.752
with their identical lives, and...

09:43.375 --> 09:46.125
They disgust me, but sometimes I...

09:47.337 --> 09:50.797
I wish I could be like that,
wish I could live like that.

09:50.882 --> 09:52.472
But I can't.

09:52.550 --> 09:54.220
I don't know what to tell you.

09:54.302 --> 09:55.512
Mom, just lie to me.

09:55.595 --> 09:58.555
- Tell me everything's gonna be all right.
- Oh...

10:03.019 --> 10:05.899
Well, I could be a secretary.

10:05.980 --> 10:07.150
[scoffs]

10:07.232 --> 10:08.982
Telephone operator.

10:09.066 --> 10:11.186
You could sell Avon like Ms. Wright.

10:11.903 --> 10:14.453
- [chuckles]
- [protestors chanting indistinctly]

10:14.531 --> 10:17.241
We're just too damn smart for these hicks.

10:17.325 --> 10:19.785
- [chanting] We will fight!
- [young Bill] What's going on?

10:21.538 --> 10:24.248
I'll bet they're going
to the White Tower restaurant.

10:24.332 --> 10:25.382
Why?

10:26.626 --> 10:28.666
Well, Billy Boy... [sighs]

10:29.712 --> 10:32.262
not all people are treated the same
in this world.

10:32.340 --> 10:34.050
Because they're non...

10:34.134 --> 10:36.224
- Noncon...
- Nonconformist?

10:36.303 --> 10:39.143
- Yeah.
- Well, you could say that, I guess.

10:39.222 --> 10:44.142
White Tower won't serve Negroes...
so they're protesting.

10:44.227 --> 10:47.307
And if they protest, will that make
the White Tower serve them?

10:47.397 --> 10:48.977
[scoffing]

10:49.899 --> 10:52.239
No, the owners of that place
are damn racists.

10:52.319 --> 10:53.949
Makes me so mad.

10:54.028 --> 10:55.948
I bet they call themselves
Christians, too.

10:56.030 --> 10:58.176
Grandpa says you might find a job
if you were more Christian.

10:58.200 --> 11:00.030
Ah, your grandpa's full of crap.

11:00.117 --> 11:01.947
Grandpa says you're the one full of crap.

11:02.036 --> 11:03.036
Excuse me?

11:03.120 --> 11:05.474
Well, you're always going on
about what's wrong with people,

11:05.498 --> 11:07.668
but you don't do anything about it.

11:07.750 --> 11:09.500
You just complain.

11:12.129 --> 11:14.129
[news theme playing]

11:20.555 --> 11:22.115
[newscaster] <i>Close to 100 demonstrators</i>

11:22.181 --> 11:25.101
<i>stepped out to protest
the whites-only policy</i>

11:25.184 --> 11:28.314
<i>of the White Tower restaurant
in downtown Baltimore.</i>

11:28.396 --> 11:30.476
<i>The activists were met
with some resistance</i>

11:30.565 --> 11:32.645
<i>from supporters of segregation.</i>

11:32.734 --> 11:37.534
[woman] <i>I think that, uh, as much</i>
<i>as we regret it, integration is here,</i>

11:37.614 --> 11:42.584
<i>and I would like to be able to do
as much as I can to prevent it coming.</i>

11:42.660 --> 11:45.250
[newscaster] <i>But one white woman</i>
<i>and her son actually showed up</i>

11:45.330 --> 11:47.210
<i>to march with the Negroes.</i>

11:47.290 --> 11:50.840
<i>The owners of the White Tower restaurant
should be ashamed of themselves.</i>

11:50.918 --> 11:53.628
<i>This is Baltimore, not Nazi Germany.</i>

11:53.713 --> 11:56.173
[newscaster] <i>And what about you,</i>
<i>young man? Why are you here?</i>

11:56.258 --> 11:58.258
[young Bill] <i>I'm here</i>
<i>because I don't like racists,</i>

11:58.343 --> 12:00.433
<i>and because I'm a nonconformist
like my mom.</i>

12:00.512 --> 12:02.142
That's my boy.

12:02.221 --> 12:04.271
What were you thinking?

12:04.349 --> 12:06.109
I was trying to teach
your grandson a lesson.

12:06.142 --> 12:08.272
"Judge not, lest ye be judged."

12:08.353 --> 12:10.313
What about the neighbors?

12:10.397 --> 12:13.477
What do you care
what nosy old Mrs. Mosley thinks?

12:13.566 --> 12:16.566
You really are one selfish SOB.

12:16.653 --> 12:19.703
Just 'cause you read
the goddamn Bible every night,

12:19.781 --> 12:22.991
you think you're
so high and mighty and moral,

12:23.075 --> 12:24.825
when there are people out there

12:24.911 --> 12:27.201
who are actually,
really, truly suffering...

12:27.289 --> 12:29.517
- You know, I've got some cold cuts...
- Mother, it's all...

12:29.541 --> 12:33.251
You have no right
to lecture me about morality.

12:33.336 --> 12:37.086
You can take your morals
and shove them up your ass.

12:37.173 --> 12:39.223
May the Lord have mercy
on your soul, Madalyn.

12:39.301 --> 12:42.141
Ooh, the Lord.
I'm quaking in my boots.

12:42.219 --> 12:44.809
Where was the Lord
when I got knocked up, huh?

12:44.889 --> 12:46.679
Where is the Lord now?

12:49.226 --> 12:51.686
[newscaster continues indistinctly]

12:53.731 --> 12:54.861
[Madalyn] What, Mother?

12:59.362 --> 13:03.032
<i>I believe we need
a spiritual revolution in America.</i>

13:03.115 --> 13:06.035
<i>We need a revolt against materialism,</i>

13:06.118 --> 13:08.198
<i>a revolt against crime,</i>

13:08.287 --> 13:11.417
<i>a revolt against the emphasis on sex,</i>

13:11.499 --> 13:12.879
<i>a revolt against the sins...</i>

13:12.959 --> 13:16.049
[Madalyn] It's like I keep telling you,
it's just case after case down there.

13:16.128 --> 13:17.189
[Mrs. Murray] Such a shame.

13:17.213 --> 13:19.763
And then I've got
this Negro girl with a baby,

13:19.841 --> 13:22.551
who got thrown out of her home,
and there is no place to put her.

13:22.635 --> 13:23.755
I mean, no place whatsoever.

13:23.845 --> 13:24.905
- We have looked...
- [Bill] Mom.

13:24.929 --> 13:27.059
Just a sec, Bill.

13:27.139 --> 13:29.929
No idea why I went into social work.

13:30.017 --> 13:31.887
I thought I could help people.

13:31.978 --> 13:33.608
But I can't.
There's too much red tape...

13:33.688 --> 13:35.207
- [Bill] Mom!
- Jesus, Mary and Joseph.

13:35.231 --> 13:36.691
I said, "Just a sec."

13:38.150 --> 13:40.610
Now you be good for Grandma, right, Garth?

13:41.488 --> 13:44.948
[Billy Graham] <i>You can find everything</i>
<i>that you've been searching for in Christ.</i>

13:45.032 --> 13:49.122
And I'd better not come home and find
my son watching that claptrap with you.

13:49.203 --> 13:51.413
I don't want him getting any ideas.

14:00.297 --> 14:01.917
I'm gonna get in trouble again.

14:02.008 --> 14:04.088
Well, it's not my fault
you missed the bus.

14:06.095 --> 14:09.965
Okay. All right, I'll talk to the teacher
if I have to, okay?

14:11.058 --> 14:14.898
[students] Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name...

14:14.979 --> 14:16.979
- We are not making a habit of this.
- I know.

14:17.064 --> 14:18.542
- You've gotta start getting up earlier.
- I know.

14:18.566 --> 14:20.226
What the hell is that?

14:20.317 --> 14:21.997
Oh, don't tell me
that's the Lord's Prayer.

14:22.069 --> 14:23.409
- Yeah.
- What are you...

14:23.488 --> 14:26.658
- You gotta be kidding me.
- They make us say it every day.

14:26.741 --> 14:28.541
- They make you read the Bible, too?
- Uh-huh.

14:28.618 --> 14:30.971
I told the teacher I don't believe
in prayer and asked to be excused.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.035
And what did she say?

14:32.121 --> 14:33.961
She said we all
have to bow our heads and pray.

14:33.998 --> 14:35.038
[groans] Oh...

14:35.124 --> 14:37.754
[all] ...and the power and the glory.

14:37.835 --> 14:39.915
- Amen.
- What the hell's going on in here?

14:40.004 --> 14:41.134
Excuse me?

14:41.213 --> 14:43.473
If I wanted my son
to learn the Lord's Prayer,

14:43.550 --> 14:45.510
I would've sent him
to goddamn Catholic school.

14:45.593 --> 14:47.473
- Mrs. Murray...
- Ms. Murray.

14:47.554 --> 14:49.564
Ms. Murray...

14:50.598 --> 14:52.138
this is our morning devotion.

14:52.224 --> 14:56.104
Well, I would like my son excused
from the morning devotion.

14:56.187 --> 14:58.187
- You don't want him to...
- Mmm-mmm.

14:58.272 --> 15:00.322
I've never heard of anything
like this in my life.

15:00.400 --> 15:02.940
Well, Mrs.... uh, Lutz, is it?

15:03.945 --> 15:06.315
My son, like myself, is an atheist.

15:06.406 --> 15:08.576
- Isn't that right, Bill?
- Uh-huh.

15:08.658 --> 15:11.868
I cannot excuse your son
from the morning devotion.

15:11.953 --> 15:15.123
It is required by the board,
and it is the law.

15:15.206 --> 15:16.536
The law?

15:16.624 --> 15:19.214
Have you heard about the Constitution,
by any chance?

15:19.293 --> 15:21.133
Kids, I hope
she's not teaching you history,

15:21.212 --> 15:23.672
because, apparently,
she flunked that class.

15:23.756 --> 15:27.046
In the Constitution, there is something
called the First Amendment.

15:27.134 --> 15:30.394
And that protects
the freedom of speech and religion.

15:30.472 --> 15:32.012
Are there any Jews in the class?

15:33.140 --> 15:36.140
Do your parents know
that you are being forced to recite

15:36.227 --> 15:38.097
- this archaic drivel?
- Ms. Murray!

15:38.187 --> 15:40.267
- I'm just trying to make a point.
- Obviously.

15:40.356 --> 15:44.896
The school board cannot force my son
to pray, or anyone else for that matter.

15:44.986 --> 15:46.856
So... sue them.

15:53.828 --> 15:58.288
First of all, can I just say,
it is wonderful to see you all again.

15:59.917 --> 16:01.627
Garth. [chuckles]

16:01.711 --> 16:03.461
Lose a few pounds?
You're looking good.

16:05.089 --> 16:07.259
Robin... did you miss me?

16:08.300 --> 16:10.890
- For fuck's sake, David, get to the point.
- Hey, I'm with you.

16:10.970 --> 16:13.390
I wanna keep this reunion
as brief as possible.

16:13.473 --> 16:15.273
So here's the deal.

16:15.349 --> 16:17.389
- Tomorrow...
- Wait, tomorrow?

16:17.477 --> 16:19.727
- What about the dogs?
- Don't worry, sweetie.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.272
Tomorrow...

16:22.273 --> 16:24.783
you're gonna write us a little check,
and then we will be happy

16:24.859 --> 16:26.859
to get you the hell out of this place.

16:26.944 --> 16:29.114
A check?
[scoffs]

16:29.196 --> 16:31.116
I'm gonna make this easy on you, Madalyn.

16:31.198 --> 16:33.488
What we want is just a drop in the bucket.

16:33.576 --> 16:35.616
[Madalyn] And what is that?

16:35.703 --> 16:36.930
- A million dollars.
- [Madalyn laughs]

16:36.954 --> 16:39.374
For fuck's sake...

16:39.456 --> 16:42.456
- It's not a fucking joke, lady.
- Uh, listen...

16:42.544 --> 16:44.384
I don't know what this guy's told you,

16:44.461 --> 16:47.841
but my organization
is a nonprofit organization.

16:47.924 --> 16:49.514
- There's no money...
- In theory,

16:49.592 --> 16:53.102
American Atheists is a nonprofit, but...
[scoffs]

16:53.179 --> 16:56.179
but we both know that there are
a few offshore accounts

16:56.265 --> 16:58.095
that will not bear that out.

17:01.145 --> 17:03.225
New Zealand, for example.

17:06.943 --> 17:08.532
[sighs heavily]

17:12.156 --> 17:14.906
- [Roy grunts] What is this shit?
- [indistinct rustling]

17:14.992 --> 17:16.742
[dog barking]

17:16.828 --> 17:18.448
- Hello?
- [knocks on door]

17:20.915 --> 17:22.244
Hello?

17:22.333 --> 17:23.383
[dogs barking loudly]

17:23.459 --> 17:24.499
Jesus.

17:27.755 --> 17:31.465
Mr. Ferguson, Roy Collier.
I work for Madalyn.

17:31.551 --> 17:33.601
Where did you get my name?

17:33.678 --> 17:37.178
You covered our protests of the courthouse
nativity scene last Christmas.

17:37.264 --> 17:38.314
[papers rustling]

17:38.390 --> 17:40.430
Thought you could use
a real story for once.

17:40.517 --> 17:42.727
And all three of them, they lived here?

17:42.812 --> 17:44.312
They were inseparable.

17:45.272 --> 17:47.192
Nobody thought that was kind of weird?

17:47.274 --> 17:50.954
Trust me, there's a lot of weird shit
going on in this family.

17:51.696 --> 17:53.446
- Mr. Ferguson...
- Call me Jack.

17:53.530 --> 17:54.820
Jack.

17:54.907 --> 17:56.867
I think something
really bad's happened here,

17:56.951 --> 17:58.751
but nobody seems to believe me.

17:58.828 --> 18:02.538
- Not even the people at American Atheists?
- [sighs] No, she's done this before.

18:02.624 --> 18:05.844
Disappeared for a few weeks,
popped up in Mexico.

18:05.918 --> 18:08.708
They think this may be
another one of her fundraising ploys.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.296
I'd be inclined to believe 'em.

18:10.381 --> 18:12.761
No, she would have left me instructions.

18:12.842 --> 18:14.972
And she never would've left
the dogs behind.

18:15.052 --> 18:18.472
Okay, look, Roy.
This isn't really my area of expertise.

18:18.555 --> 18:19.765
Then why did you come?

18:19.849 --> 18:22.059
Well, I thought
there might be a story here.

18:23.811 --> 18:24.811
Jackpot.

18:29.734 --> 18:31.114
Passports.

18:37.241 --> 18:39.871
Still doesn't prove
that they're not just out of town.

18:41.663 --> 18:44.083
Okay, let's say you're right.
Let's say they were kidnapped.

18:44.165 --> 18:45.825
- Or worse.
- What about Robin's father?

18:45.917 --> 18:46.917
- Bill Jr.?
- Yeah.

18:47.001 --> 18:49.211
He hasn't spoken to his family in years.

18:49.295 --> 18:51.705
His ass won't even
file a missing person's report.

18:51.798 --> 18:53.651
Well, then he should be
at the top of your list.

18:53.675 --> 18:54.795
No. No.

18:54.884 --> 18:59.184
Bill and his mom may have had some issues,
but he would never do anything like this.

19:00.973 --> 19:02.103
Well, then, who would?

19:03.017 --> 19:04.477
Are you kidding?

19:04.560 --> 19:08.060
Do you know how many death threats
this woman would receive in a day?

19:09.398 --> 19:10.438
No.

19:12.276 --> 19:14.566
[woman speaking indistinctly on phone]

19:15.697 --> 19:16.817
Sure.

19:16.906 --> 19:18.826
No. Right.
Uh, no, I know.

19:18.908 --> 19:20.028
Well, I...

19:21.160 --> 19:25.330
Oh. Yeah. No, I... I do know Mr. Epstein
from the Austin branch, right?

19:25.414 --> 19:26.714
Garth, come on.

19:26.791 --> 19:28.671
[Madalyn] Good morning.

19:28.751 --> 19:30.291
Okay.
Uh-huh.

19:30.377 --> 19:33.257
[stammers] Yup. Right, we'll talk then.
Bye-bye. Mmm-hmm.

19:36.383 --> 19:38.013
So... [sighs]

19:40.262 --> 19:42.432
I can only get $600,000.

19:42.514 --> 19:44.684
That's what's in our personal account.

19:44.767 --> 19:45.807
What?

19:46.602 --> 19:47.942
Where is the rest of it?

19:48.020 --> 19:49.770
It's in dummy trusts.

19:50.732 --> 19:52.692
It's in dummy what now?

19:53.693 --> 19:57.113
They have to wire it here, the 600 grand,
from New Zealand next week.

19:57.196 --> 19:58.196
Next week?

19:58.280 --> 20:00.410
And I have to sign for it in person.

20:00.491 --> 20:01.491
[Gary] Hey...

20:03.327 --> 20:04.327
Are you lying?

20:05.079 --> 20:06.749
Gary, calm down.

20:06.831 --> 20:09.211
I'm calm.
He's a big boy.

20:09.291 --> 20:11.591
You didn't plan this very well,
did you, David?

20:12.169 --> 20:14.589
I am in no mood for a jerk-off contest.

20:15.172 --> 20:17.592
Do I need to remind you
who's holding the guns here?

20:19.676 --> 20:24.016
Everybody just needs to settle in...
and try and get along.

20:24.098 --> 20:26.768
Looks like we're gonna be
roommates for a few days.

20:27.351 --> 20:28.391
[Garth sighs]

20:28.477 --> 20:31.397
You don't think
the police are gonna be looking for me?

20:31.480 --> 20:34.860
No, Madalyn, I don't think
anyone's gonna be looking for you.

20:34.942 --> 20:36.282
[Madalyn sighs]

20:39.238 --> 20:40.778
[phone ringing]

20:42.867 --> 20:43.987
William Murray Jr.

20:44.076 --> 20:47.196
Mr. Murray, Jack Ferguson,
<i>San Antonio Daily Journal.</i>

20:47.288 --> 20:49.668
I don't give quotes on my mother,
Mr. Ferguson.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.879
<i>- I assume that's what you're after.</i>
- Uh, sort of.

20:51.959 --> 20:54.129
I'm looking into
your family's disappearance.

20:54.211 --> 20:55.301
<i>Roy Collier call you?</i>

20:56.005 --> 20:57.705
Let me give you some advice, Mr. Ferguson.

20:57.799 --> 20:58.799
<i>Don't waste your time.</i>

20:58.883 --> 21:00.986
<i>You don't wanna look like a fool
when they suddenly show up.</i>

21:01.010 --> 21:02.445
Roy seems to think this is different.

21:02.469 --> 21:05.559
Well, I guess it's possible
they finally left the country for good.

21:05.639 --> 21:08.519
<i>They've been putting money
from American Atheists</i>

21:08.600 --> 21:09.920
<i>into offshore accounts for years.</i>

21:09.977 --> 21:11.307
Embezzlement?

21:11.395 --> 21:13.555
<i>My mother prefers to call it
"creative accounting."</i>

21:13.647 --> 21:15.000
<i>Now, if you'll excuse me, Mr. Ferguson...</i>

21:15.024 --> 21:16.324
Uh, one question.

21:16.400 --> 21:18.530
The dogs...

21:18.610 --> 21:20.530
Roy said that they took them everywhere.

21:20.612 --> 21:22.674
Sure, she treats those things
better than her own family.

21:22.698 --> 21:26.198
<i>Well, that's why he's so worried.
They left them behind.</i>

21:28.245 --> 21:29.575
Goodbye, Mr. Ferguson.

21:35.502 --> 21:38.842
[newscaster] <i>Communist guerrillas,</i>
<i>hiding out in the brush.</i>

21:38.923 --> 21:41.151
<i>Skirmishes such as this
have been plaguing the country...</i>

21:41.175 --> 21:42.610
[Mrs. Murray] Madalyn,
I just don't get this.

21:42.634 --> 21:46.394
I still can't understand why those
children can't say one little prayer.

21:46.472 --> 21:49.182
They can pray all they want to.

21:49.266 --> 21:52.016
- School can't force 'em to.
- Okay, Maddy.

21:52.103 --> 21:53.563
But can't somebody else fight this?

21:53.645 --> 21:55.265
Why does it always have to be you?

21:55.356 --> 21:56.976
Why not me?

21:57.066 --> 21:58.896
- [sighs]
- This is important.

21:58.985 --> 22:00.735
I'm just so worried about Pup.

22:00.820 --> 22:03.200
His health isn't what it used to be.

22:03.280 --> 22:05.660
Well, he better start a-goddamn prayin',

22:05.741 --> 22:08.791
'cause we're gonna take this all the way
to the Supreme Court if we have to.

22:08.870 --> 22:10.513
- [man] Your mother's a whore!
- [glass shattering]

22:10.537 --> 22:12.182
- [Bill] Get the hell off of me!
- [door opens]

22:12.206 --> 22:14.036
- [Mrs. Murray] Oh, Billy.
- [door closes]

22:14.125 --> 22:16.625
[man] Go to hell, commies!
No one wants you.

22:16.710 --> 22:18.920
- You go to hell!
- Go, go, go!

22:19.005 --> 22:20.045
[Pup] Madalyn!

22:24.176 --> 22:25.506
[Madalyn sighs]

22:38.357 --> 22:40.187
Come on. [sighs]

22:41.110 --> 22:42.440
Why didn't you tell me?

22:42.528 --> 22:43.568
The kids at school?

22:43.654 --> 22:45.414
- Mmm.
- I can handle it.

22:45.489 --> 22:48.159
- Oh, you think so?
- Yeah, they ambushed me.

22:49.618 --> 22:51.868
Still got a few good elbows
in there, though.

22:53.580 --> 22:55.210
What about the teachers?

22:56.292 --> 22:58.462
- They're ignoring me.
- [scoffs]

22:58.544 --> 23:00.214
They won't call on me anymore.

23:04.425 --> 23:07.255
I don't know, Billy Boy.
Maybe we oughta drop this.

23:09.305 --> 23:11.515
I don't wanna have to worry about you.

23:11.598 --> 23:13.308
Your name is on this lawsuit.

23:13.392 --> 23:15.312
This fight, it's gotta be your choice.

23:17.021 --> 23:18.151
Mom...

23:19.065 --> 23:20.475
we're in this together.

23:22.109 --> 23:24.109
Nonconformists, remember?

23:25.862 --> 23:27.662
Nonconformists.

23:29.533 --> 23:33.293
Sweetie, we pull this off,
we're gonna be goddamn revolutionaries.

23:34.205 --> 23:36.205
- [chuckles]
- [both sniffle]

23:38.500 --> 23:41.229
[newscaster] David Brinkley's Journal,
<i>usually presented at this time,</i>

23:41.253 --> 23:42.713
<i>will not be seen tonight,</i>

23:42.796 --> 23:45.546
<i>so that we may bring you
the following special program.</i>

23:46.342 --> 23:49.602
[reporter] <i>Washington, DC,</i>
<i>June 17th, 1963.</i>

23:50.346 --> 23:53.056
<i>An 8-1 decision of the US Supreme Court</i>

23:53.140 --> 23:55.770
<i>declared prayer in school
unconstitutional.</i>

23:55.851 --> 23:58.061
<i>The judgment, the results
of a case against</i>

23:58.145 --> 23:59.935
<i>the Baltimore public school system,</i>

24:00.022 --> 24:01.732
<i>stirred protests across the nation.</i>

24:01.815 --> 24:05.145
<i>Today's decision is offensive
to everyone...</i>

24:05.236 --> 24:08.156
<i>who wishes to keep
this a religious nation.</i>

24:08.780 --> 24:11.030
[reporter] <i>As demonstrators</i>
<i>ascended on the capital,</i>

24:11.117 --> 24:14.577
<i>President Kennedy did his best
to defuse the controversy.</i>

24:14.661 --> 24:19.461
<i>I think that, uh, it is important for us
that we, uh...</i>

24:19.541 --> 24:23.881
<i>support Supreme Court decisions
even when we may not agree with them.</i>

24:23.962 --> 24:26.972
<i>In addition, we have in this case
a very easy remedy.</i>

24:27.049 --> 24:29.719
<i>And that is to pray, ourselves.</i>

24:29.801 --> 24:31.238
[reporter] <i>The plaintiffs in the case,</i>

24:31.262 --> 24:35.352
<i>self-described atheists Madalyn Murray
and her teenage son Bill,</i>

24:35.432 --> 24:36.482
<i>were unapologetic.</i>

24:36.558 --> 24:38.598
<i>I don't understand
why people are so upset.</i>

24:38.685 --> 24:42.145
<i>- This is about religious freedom.</i>
- [people shouting]

24:42.231 --> 24:44.481
<i>You can still keep the faith, people.</i>

24:44.566 --> 24:46.026
<i>Just keep it to yourselves.</i>

24:49.155 --> 24:50.735
[doorbell rings]

24:53.200 --> 24:55.410
Ooh, this is a good one.

24:57.038 --> 24:58.538
"The next thing you know,

24:58.622 --> 25:02.962
Madalyn Murray will force the country
to eliminate 'one nation under God'

25:03.044 --> 25:04.924
from the Pledge of Allegiance."

25:05.837 --> 25:07.957
It's actually not a bad idea.

25:08.049 --> 25:10.089
We should be clipping coupons,
not articles.

25:10.176 --> 25:11.176
Oh, pfft.

25:11.260 --> 25:14.060
I cannot believe
that the Family Aid Society fired you.

25:14.138 --> 25:17.018
Well, I was a disgrace
to the city of Baltimore. Remember?

25:17.099 --> 25:19.689
Besides, I couldn't get
crap done there, anyway.

25:19.768 --> 25:20.888
Here comes the hate mail.

25:20.977 --> 25:23.147
Mother, it's not all bad.

25:25.316 --> 25:26.686
Thanks, sweetie.

25:28.152 --> 25:30.112
Mmm.
[inhales deeply]

25:30.946 --> 25:32.316
[exclaims] What...

25:33.115 --> 25:36.825
"Here's shit in your eye."

25:37.744 --> 25:40.124
Well, they got wit.
I'll give 'em that, at least.

25:40.206 --> 25:41.666
- Here, let me get it.
- No.

25:41.748 --> 25:43.788
It's a good photo.
I'm gonna keep it.

25:47.088 --> 25:48.168
Ah, see.

25:48.255 --> 25:50.715
Now there's someone who appreciates me.
Hmm?

25:58.307 --> 26:00.097
The Lord will provide.

26:00.184 --> 26:01.904
[Mrs. Murray] That'll buy us
some groceries.

26:10.902 --> 26:13.112
Ooh, good fella.
Get me another one.

26:28.129 --> 26:29.459
[chuckles]

26:31.673 --> 26:34.843
[newscaster] <i>Madalyn Murray, the woman</i>
<i>who expelled prayer from schools,</i>

26:34.926 --> 26:37.096
<i>is stirring things up again.</i>

26:37.179 --> 26:39.679
<i>She held a rally
at the University of Baltimore</i>

26:39.765 --> 26:42.885
<i>to promote her new organization,
American Atheists.</i>

26:42.976 --> 26:45.596
[Madalyn] <i>I'm not trying</i>
<i>to convert anyone here.</i>

26:45.687 --> 26:47.557
<i>And at no time have I said</i>

26:47.648 --> 26:51.188
<i>that people should be stripped
of their right to believe in God.</i>

26:51.277 --> 26:53.107
<i>But as an atheist,</i>

26:53.195 --> 26:56.865
<i>I believe a good deed should be done
instead of a prayer said,</i>

26:56.948 --> 26:59.238
<i>a hospital built instead of a church.</i>

26:59.326 --> 27:04.536
<i>We want disease conquered,
poverty vanished and war eliminated.</i>

27:04.623 --> 27:05.833
[applause]

27:18.637 --> 27:21.137
- Another check.
- Ooh. [chuckles]

27:27.396 --> 27:29.186
[newscaster] <i>Mad Madalyn is at it again,</i>

27:29.273 --> 27:32.533
<i>this time filing suit
with the Baltimore public school system</i>

27:32.609 --> 27:35.739
<i>to remove the words "under God"
from the Pledge of Allegiance.</i>

27:35.821 --> 27:38.201
<i>Well, we sure as hell
aren't gonna win this one.</i>

27:38.282 --> 27:40.082
<i>But it's a fight worth having.</i>

27:51.878 --> 27:52.918
Shit!

28:12.107 --> 28:13.357
[laughs]

28:26.121 --> 28:28.251
"Page Si..." Page six?

28:28.332 --> 28:30.752
[Frank] The police haven't even opened
an investigation yet.

28:30.834 --> 28:31.894
And there are plenty of people

28:31.918 --> 28:33.771
who'd just as soon never see
that woman in Texas again.

28:33.795 --> 28:35.335
Well, can I at least have a follow-up?

28:35.422 --> 28:38.512
Right now, I need a story
on the transit board's bus route overhaul.

28:39.843 --> 28:41.053
Thanks, buddy.

28:44.390 --> 28:45.640
[sighs]

28:52.606 --> 28:54.186
This is all they had.

28:55.609 --> 28:57.319
I think you look pretty hot.

28:59.280 --> 29:01.280
[Madalyn] Hey, Gary, ever occur to you

29:01.365 --> 29:06.745
that your sole purpose in life might be
to serve as an argument for birth control?

29:06.828 --> 29:08.788
You know what? Just...
Just ignore her.

29:08.872 --> 29:10.292
There you are.

29:10.374 --> 29:14.424
A little overcooked,
just like you like them.

29:14.503 --> 29:16.213
[Madalyn] You remembered.

29:16.297 --> 29:19.507
I figured the least we could do
if we're all stuck here together

29:19.591 --> 29:20.631
is be civil.

29:20.717 --> 29:23.297
I wouldn't spit in your ass
if your guts were on fire.

29:23.387 --> 29:25.807
- That civil enough for you?
- [David] Oh, come on.

29:25.889 --> 29:28.479
I'm having a good time.
Who else is having a good time?

29:28.559 --> 29:30.809
- Uh, yeah, sure. I guess.
- Garth.

29:30.894 --> 29:32.774
I mean, he got us video games.

29:32.854 --> 29:36.784
He's right. I brought your medicine,
I got you a change of clothes.

29:36.858 --> 29:41.488
I... I'd say for kidnappers,
we are damn near hospitable.

29:41.572 --> 29:43.952
This is much better than prison, trust me.

29:44.032 --> 29:47.242
[scoffs] Gary was in prison.
How come I didn't see that coming?

29:48.244 --> 29:50.584
You know, you just can't seem
to shut the fuck up.

29:50.664 --> 29:54.544
I bet you saw more cock in the slammer
than a urinal at the Astrodome.

29:54.626 --> 29:56.187
- [David] Hey, hey, hey!
- Oh, go ahead and shoot me.

29:56.211 --> 29:58.131
I'm an awfully big body to hide.

29:58.213 --> 29:59.973
- Gary, put the gun away.
- Open up, Grandma!

30:00.048 --> 30:01.718
- Keep talking.
- [Robin] Gary...

30:01.800 --> 30:05.100
- No, be funny, fucking Grandma. Do it!
