45:39.529 --> 45:40.989
The New Testament?

45:41.071 --> 45:44.621
Oh, a load of bull
written by a bunch of faggots.

45:44.700 --> 45:47.620
- Oh, come on. Y'all know that.
- [audience jeering]

45:47.703 --> 45:49.793
Jesus was as queer as a three-dollar bill.

45:49.872 --> 45:51.502
[woman] You dirty heathen!

45:51.582 --> 45:55.382
[Madalyn] Mmm-hmm?
Let me see what that looks like.

45:55.461 --> 45:57.591
Yeah. Oh, that's not bad.

45:57.672 --> 46:00.722
[Bob] You were on fire
out there tonight, darlin'. [chuckles]

46:00.800 --> 46:04.430
Every time you tear into this Bible,
I save another 50 souls.

46:04.512 --> 46:06.182
Yeah, I know you like that bit.

46:06.263 --> 46:09.143
I do. Why don't you let me see
how the numbers are here?

46:10.560 --> 46:13.400
Oh, not bad.
We'll do better in Kansas City.

46:13.479 --> 46:15.819
I'll burn the goddamn book in Kansas City.

46:15.898 --> 46:18.188
- Oh, Praise the Lord!
- [laughing]

46:18.275 --> 46:20.105
Thank you, Garth. [chuckles]

46:20.194 --> 46:22.074
I'll keep praying for your soul, Madalyn.

46:22.154 --> 46:24.034
I'll keep cursing yours.

46:24.114 --> 46:26.084
You think we won anyone over?

46:26.867 --> 46:28.697
Oh, I don't know, honey.

46:31.080 --> 46:32.670
Did you hear from your father?

46:34.166 --> 46:39.336
Oh, he'll be back when he's shitfaced
and needs his ass wiped. [chuckles]

46:41.298 --> 46:44.968
He just needed a little break.
We'll see him again soon enough.

46:45.886 --> 46:49.596
Hey, when all this is over,
how about we take a little trip, huh?

46:49.682 --> 46:51.535
[Bill] <i>I spent the last 20 years</i>
<i>trying to escape</i>

46:51.559 --> 46:54.559
<i>the overpowering shadow of my mother.</i>

46:56.397 --> 46:57.517
[sighs]

46:58.733 --> 47:03.573
While she was fighting the world...
I was fighting for my life.

47:07.074 --> 47:10.084
I didn't realize
how bad it had gotten till...

47:10.160 --> 47:12.080
I got out of Austin and...

47:13.038 --> 47:14.998
started locking myself
in the bathroom every night

47:15.082 --> 47:18.292
with a bottle of whiskey
and a bucket of ice.

47:22.297 --> 47:24.217
And then one night, I...

47:26.677 --> 47:28.757
I had this sudden rush of sorrow.

47:34.935 --> 47:36.345
Because I understood.

47:37.354 --> 47:42.114
I understood the, uh... the hatred

47:42.192 --> 47:46.952
and the... the self-pity
that she was feeling.

47:49.450 --> 47:51.330
Because that's what I was feeling.

47:58.208 --> 48:00.038
But I come here, and I...

48:01.295 --> 48:03.005
I see others,

48:03.088 --> 48:05.048
much worse situations than me, and...

48:05.966 --> 48:10.256
you overcome, and you accept them.

48:12.347 --> 48:13.717
And that, uh...

48:17.728 --> 48:19.188
That's what I'm gonna do.

48:23.734 --> 48:25.574
[group] Our Father...

48:25.653 --> 48:29.243
[Bill] ...who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.

48:29.323 --> 48:31.533
[all] Thy kingdom come,

48:31.617 --> 48:34.947
thy will be done,
on earth as it is in heaven.

48:36.163 --> 48:41.343
Give us this day our daily bread,
forgive us our trespasses,

48:41.418 --> 48:44.208
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

48:45.214 --> 48:49.554
And lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

48:50.302 --> 48:55.482
For thine is the kingdom and the power
and the glory...

48:55.558 --> 48:57.268
forever and ever...

48:57.351 --> 48:59.231
[group] Amen.

48:59.311 --> 49:00.521
[Bill] Amen.

49:04.066 --> 49:07.236
Frank, I need another day
on the Riverwalk article.

49:07.319 --> 49:08.964
I just got a new lead on the O'Hair story.

49:08.988 --> 49:09.988
- Frank, listen.
- Jack...

49:10.072 --> 49:12.622
Robin Murray's Porsche
just turned up abandoned at the airport

49:12.700 --> 49:16.450
and Garth's car sold to some guy
out by Canyon Lake. I mean, come on.

49:18.623 --> 49:20.173
Follow it up.

49:20.249 --> 49:22.289
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

49:22.376 --> 49:24.456
Frank! I love you!

49:27.464 --> 49:28.804
All right.

49:30.843 --> 49:32.973
[man] Nope.
I didn't buy it from him.

49:33.053 --> 49:35.183
- You sure?
- Positive.

49:35.264 --> 49:38.314
It was a short guy.
He was younger, had dark hair.

49:38.392 --> 49:40.442
All right.
If I sent a sketch artist to your house,

49:40.520 --> 49:42.200
would you be willing to sit down with him?

49:42.271 --> 49:45.731
- Sure. [sighs]
- Thanks, Mr. Sparrow.

49:47.484 --> 49:49.034
I don't get it.

49:49.111 --> 49:52.071
What kind of religious nut
goes off and sells a stolen car?

49:52.156 --> 49:54.366
Well, maybe this isn't the work
of a religious nut.

49:54.449 --> 49:55.659
What do you mean?

49:56.451 --> 49:59.451
Well, Madalyn was stashing
loads of cash, right?

49:59.539 --> 50:00.669
Mmm.

50:00.748 --> 50:02.998
Makes for the greatest motive of all.

50:03.918 --> 50:04.998
Greed.

50:11.341 --> 50:13.641
This is just like the old days.

50:14.679 --> 50:16.759
You used to let me win.

50:18.348 --> 50:20.518
You were the boss.
I had to.

50:21.686 --> 50:24.096
Does that mean
I'm supposed to let you win now?

50:24.188 --> 50:25.518
You do have the gun.

50:26.982 --> 50:30.702
And we all know what that means.
Compensating for a very small cock.

50:30.778 --> 50:32.488
- Right, Red?
- [both chuckle]

50:32.572 --> 50:34.507
- That's what you always say, Grandma.
- [Madalyn chuckles]

50:34.531 --> 50:36.951
Oh, come on, Madalyn.
You can do better than that.

50:37.034 --> 50:40.334
I don't waste my best lines
on small-time crooks.

50:41.496 --> 50:44.366
You're just as much of a crook as I am,

50:44.458 --> 50:47.088
rippin' people off
in the name of your cause.

50:47.169 --> 50:48.419
That is bullcrap!

50:49.379 --> 50:53.929
I have devoted my life
to protecting the First Amendment.

50:55.052 --> 50:57.052
The things I've had to endure.

50:58.472 --> 51:01.022
Made a little money along the way.
I deserve it.

51:01.100 --> 51:02.270
You are so full of yourself,

51:02.351 --> 51:05.351
you can't see
the fucking forest for the trees.

51:06.731 --> 51:08.861
While you're out fighting the world,

51:08.941 --> 51:11.991
you're making real enemies
right under your nose.

51:12.069 --> 51:16.119
You get a load of that, Red?
David Waters is lecturing me.

51:16.198 --> 51:17.318
[Madalyn laughs]

51:17.407 --> 51:21.117
Your own son would tell you
the exact same thing.

51:21.203 --> 51:22.373
And...

51:25.374 --> 51:26.504
gin.

51:29.920 --> 51:31.130
[sighs]

51:34.008 --> 51:37.008
<i>I led a life wasted
without faith in the Lord.</i>

51:38.804 --> 51:42.274
<i>And I hope I can right
some of the wrongs I caused.</i>

51:42.349 --> 51:45.059
<i>I see my mother as a sinner now.</i>

51:45.144 --> 51:50.614
<i>She demanded things of God,
and when he refused her requests, well...</i>

51:50.691 --> 51:52.481
<i>she began to battle with him openly.</i>

51:53.736 --> 51:57.946
<i>Now all she cares about is...
getting wealthy by hating God.</i>

51:58.573 --> 52:00.093
[interviewer] <i>Do you love your mother?</i>

52:00.159 --> 52:02.829
[Bill] <i>Oh, I love my mother.</i>
<i>I forgive my mother.</i>

52:03.829 --> 52:06.209
<i>But I'm not proud
of what she did to this country.</i>

52:06.290 --> 52:07.650
[interviewer] <i>Do you pray for her?</i>

52:07.708 --> 52:09.168
[Bill] <i>I wish I could pray for her.</i>

52:09.251 --> 52:10.251
Turn it off.

52:10.335 --> 52:12.415
[Bill] <i>But I'm afraid</i>
<i>it wouldn't do any good.</i>

52:16.759 --> 52:19.799
Sold out to the highest bidder,
the goddamn church.

52:22.431 --> 52:23.471
Mother.

52:24.975 --> 52:27.635
I've been called
every dirty name in the book.

52:27.728 --> 52:30.478
There's not a day goes by
without a death threat.

52:32.858 --> 52:35.608
None of it hurt, but this...
This...

52:36.528 --> 52:37.608
[thumps table]

52:40.991 --> 52:43.331
Garth, am I really that bad of a mother?

52:44.494 --> 52:45.664
No.

52:46.663 --> 52:49.963
Mother, I will always be here.

52:52.962 --> 52:55.672
- We'll both always be here.
- [Madalyn] Oh...

52:56.841 --> 52:58.261
[sighs]

53:00.761 --> 53:02.051
[sniffles]

53:06.100 --> 53:07.430
[phone ringing]

53:09.561 --> 53:10.901
Mr. Waters.

53:16.902 --> 53:17.952
[Madalyn] Thank you, Roy.

53:19.571 --> 53:21.821
- Ms. O'Hair, it is a pleasure.
- [laughs]

53:21.907 --> 53:24.737
Oh, well, have a seat.
[clears throat]

53:25.660 --> 53:27.660
I saw you on <i>Carson</i> last week.

53:27.747 --> 53:31.037
[chuckles] I love the way
you shut Billy Graham up.

53:31.125 --> 53:34.625
Oh, thank you.
It was a little easier than it looked.

53:34.711 --> 53:35.881
Now you're just being modest.

53:35.963 --> 53:39.133
That preacher's more full of shit
than a Christmas turkey, that's for sure.

53:39.216 --> 53:42.636
Oh, hell, he's more full of shit
than a goddamn humpback whale!

53:42.719 --> 53:44.259
[both laughing]

53:46.891 --> 53:52.731
So... you're here about the, uh,
office management position?

53:52.813 --> 53:55.983
- [clicks tongue] Yes, ma'am.
- Yeah, you sure you, uh, wanna join us?

53:56.066 --> 53:58.026
Right now, we're holding
this place together

53:58.110 --> 53:59.570
with bailing wire and chewing gum.

53:59.653 --> 54:02.243
I have held together more with less.

54:02.322 --> 54:06.292
My son, Bill, he used to, uh,
run the place.

54:06.368 --> 54:09.748
But, uh... he screwed me over.

54:12.041 --> 54:16.551
Oh, now those goddamn zombie
twelve-steppers got a hold of him and...

54:17.797 --> 54:20.417
Do you, uh, drink, Mr. Waters?

54:21.508 --> 54:24.178
I do have a few of the usual vices.

54:24.261 --> 54:25.261
Oh, good.

54:27.181 --> 54:30.391
'Cause I do not go in
for that teetotalin' crap.

54:30.475 --> 54:31.975
[both chuckle]

54:35.397 --> 54:37.067
There we go.

54:37.149 --> 54:38.319
Here's to.

54:40.945 --> 54:41.945
[David sighs]

54:42.029 --> 54:47.659
It has been mentioned that you, uh...
spent some time in the Illinois State Pen.

54:49.036 --> 54:53.116
[stammers] Just a few petty crimes...
when I was younger.

54:56.793 --> 54:57.923
Well...

54:59.338 --> 55:04.628
if Hail Marys really could absolve us...
we'd all be goddamn murderers.

55:05.385 --> 55:07.255
[both chuckle]

55:10.182 --> 55:13.732
Now the first thing she wants you to do
is help get the books in order.

55:13.810 --> 55:17.020
We usually get the statements from
Bank of Austin on the third of the month.

55:17.106 --> 55:19.016
This is where we keep the ledger.

55:19.108 --> 55:22.738
You'll have the only key, besides me.

55:23.904 --> 55:27.074
You'll register all processed checks here.

55:27.157 --> 55:29.157
Wait, these are all donations?

55:29.243 --> 55:30.243
That's right.

55:31.620 --> 55:35.750
There's a check here for $20,000.
Another for 12.

55:35.832 --> 55:37.172
I know.

55:37.251 --> 55:40.461
In God we trust.
Right?

55:40.545 --> 55:42.915
[both laughing]

55:43.840 --> 55:45.300
[Roy grunts and sighs]

55:46.218 --> 55:47.588
Ooh! Mmm.

55:49.721 --> 55:51.101
Good luck.

55:58.647 --> 56:00.607
[Madalyn sighs]

56:02.943 --> 56:04.653
Mmm, what's going on?

56:04.736 --> 56:06.406
The money made it out of New Zealand.

56:06.488 --> 56:07.908
[groaning]

56:08.865 --> 56:09.865
[grunts]

56:11.160 --> 56:12.660
It won't be long now.

56:16.456 --> 56:18.376
[chuckles] It's about time.

56:22.296 --> 56:23.666
The van's out back.

56:25.674 --> 56:27.384
Garth...

56:27.467 --> 56:31.637
you try anything... anything,
Madalyn and Robin are dead.

56:31.721 --> 56:33.061
No, I got it.

56:33.140 --> 56:34.180
Let's go.

56:36.393 --> 56:37.393
Bye, Mother.

56:37.477 --> 56:39.897
- You be careful, Garth.
- [Garth] Okay.

56:45.694 --> 56:48.864
You know those bills are gonna be marked.
[scoffs]

56:48.948 --> 56:50.568
They're getting a cashier's check.

56:50.657 --> 56:51.827
[Madalyn scoffs]

56:51.908 --> 56:56.868
Then we're using that to buy gold coins.
Something that can't be traced.

57:01.335 --> 57:03.915
- Here you go, Grandma.
- Thank you, darlin'.

57:05.922 --> 57:07.722
[groans softly]

57:12.471 --> 57:14.931
Well, it looks like
you might have me here.

57:16.600 --> 57:17.600
'Night.

57:21.981 --> 57:23.901
[mutters] Wait a minute.

57:26.526 --> 57:27.606
[chuckles]

57:28.528 --> 57:29.898
Gin.

57:32.282 --> 57:33.622
You'll win next time.

57:33.700 --> 57:34.802
- [scoffing] Yeah.
- [chuckling]

57:34.826 --> 57:36.906
Sure, I'll win one of these days.

57:41.125 --> 57:43.495
You've done a real good job here, David.

57:44.503 --> 57:45.923
But, uh...

57:46.838 --> 57:49.128
I want you to know I did some, uh...

57:50.550 --> 57:51.590
digging...

57:52.511 --> 57:53.971
into your record.

57:56.556 --> 57:58.806
True you were picked up for hustling?

58:03.772 --> 58:06.902
I told you I am trying
to put all that behind me.

58:08.652 --> 58:11.032
I don't give a shit
what you do with your pecker.

58:12.322 --> 58:13.742
But, David...

58:16.243 --> 58:17.453
you killed a man.

58:21.331 --> 58:22.621
Now, tell me about him.

58:24.751 --> 58:26.051
Just between us.

58:28.088 --> 58:29.088
Hmm?

58:31.258 --> 58:33.718
I didn't have a picture-perfect childhood,
Madalyn.

58:35.804 --> 58:37.434
My mother was a prostitute.

58:38.973 --> 58:42.193
And she was in and out of prison
so much that I'd do

58:42.269 --> 58:45.019
whatever I had to do to survive.

58:46.023 --> 58:47.153
[sighs]

58:47.232 --> 58:50.782
I hooked up with this gang.
I started stealing here and there, and...

58:51.361 --> 58:55.281
this guy we were with got caught
after this liquor store job we did.

58:56.408 --> 58:57.658
He turned on me.

58:58.743 --> 59:00.453
[chuckles]

59:00.537 --> 59:04.037
I may not believe in God,
but I do believe in karma.

59:05.084 --> 59:07.044
All that crap about past lives?

59:08.212 --> 59:09.212
Yeah, well...

59:11.798 --> 59:13.218
maybe not karma.

59:17.512 --> 59:18.682
Retaliation.

59:21.516 --> 59:23.096
I was gonna teach this guy a lesson.

59:24.478 --> 59:26.978
But when I started with that tire iron...

59:28.398 --> 59:30.188
I don't know, I just...

59:32.694 --> 59:34.204
I lost control.

59:38.117 --> 59:40.907
[sighs] I got 30 years,
but I only did half.

59:42.036 --> 59:43.326
Got out for good behavior.

59:44.748 --> 59:47.418
And I swore
I would never lose control again.

59:52.297 --> 59:53.337
Thank you.

59:54.633 --> 59:55.683
Mmm-hmm.

59:57.051 --> 01:00:00.891
Thank you for telling me
the fucking truth.

01:00:03.100 --> 01:00:04.600
[scoffs]

01:00:04.684 --> 01:00:08.114
Yeah, you live long enough
and you lose faith in people.

01:00:08.188 --> 01:00:11.438
- Not that I ever had much faith in anyone.
- [chuckles]

01:00:11.525 --> 01:00:12.645
But...

01:00:15.279 --> 01:00:16.949
you have impressed me, David.

01:00:19.408 --> 01:00:22.868
Starting to wish Bill Jr.
Could've turned out more like you.

01:00:23.953 --> 01:00:25.713
He really hurt you, huh?

01:00:28.041 --> 01:00:29.671
He betrayed me.

01:00:29.751 --> 01:00:32.711
That's what men do.
Betray me.

01:00:38.302 --> 01:00:42.262
But, no, David, he didn't hurt me.

01:00:43.682 --> 01:00:45.642
Nobody can really hurt me.

01:00:50.147 --> 01:00:53.857
Now that I trust you,
I wanna show you something.

01:01:01.408 --> 01:01:03.488
I'm giving you a promotion, David.

01:01:03.577 --> 01:01:08.327
So far, you've been keeping track
of most of our donations

01:01:08.415 --> 01:01:11.915
in the official ledger book.

01:01:12.001 --> 01:01:15.381
I say most of them because...

01:01:15.464 --> 01:01:18.594
this is our unofficial ledger.

01:01:21.761 --> 01:01:24.391
I'll keep your secrets, you keep mine.

01:01:26.558 --> 01:01:28.808
[both chuckle]

01:01:33.523 --> 01:01:34.573
[knock on door]

01:01:34.649 --> 01:01:35.939
[door opens]

01:01:39.613 --> 01:01:41.113
[Gary sighs]

01:01:54.836 --> 01:01:55.836
Where are the rest?

01:01:55.920 --> 01:01:57.260
In the trunk.

01:01:58.172 --> 01:02:00.972
Well, at least $400,000 of it is.

01:02:03.512 --> 01:02:06.472
Four hundred?
Gary, what the hell?

01:02:06.556 --> 01:02:09.136
The fucking guy didn't have enough.

01:02:11.060 --> 01:02:13.150
We get the rest next week.

01:02:15.524 --> 01:02:16.824
Shit.

01:02:19.403 --> 01:02:20.403
Shit.

01:02:21.488 --> 01:02:23.988
Shit! Shit! Shit! Shit! Shit!

01:02:24.073 --> 01:02:25.913
[grunting]

01:02:29.496 --> 01:02:31.666
Is that really necessary?

01:02:31.748 --> 01:02:34.128
Oh, don't tell me it's another hiccup.
[scoffs]

01:02:34.208 --> 01:02:36.145
[Garth] We have to wait
for another shipment of coins.

01:02:36.169 --> 01:02:37.169
What?

01:02:37.254 --> 01:02:39.054
They'll be here next Tuesday.

01:02:39.130 --> 01:02:41.930
Oh, for...
This is getting ridiculous.

01:02:42.759 --> 01:02:46.099
- Shut up. You're not in charge here.
- [Madalyn laughing]

01:02:46.179 --> 01:02:49.269
All right, I got it. I got it.
You're the big boss.

01:02:49.349 --> 01:02:52.439
But God damn it, David,
if you aren't fucking up this job

01:02:52.519 --> 01:02:53.913
like everything else you've ever done.

01:02:53.937 --> 01:02:55.357
Mother!

01:02:55.439 --> 01:02:57.269
Oh, pfft.
Ahh!

01:02:57.357 --> 01:03:00.567
If I shot you in the head right now,
do you think anyone would care?

01:03:00.652 --> 01:03:03.782
The state of Texas would probably
give me a fucking medal.

01:03:13.707 --> 01:03:14.827
Look at this.

01:03:16.376 --> 01:03:19.496
$625,000 is missing
from the New Zealand account.

01:03:20.672 --> 01:03:22.592
Withdrawn right after they disappeared.

01:03:38.315 --> 01:03:40.725
I say we take the coins we've got
and get out of town.

01:03:41.818 --> 01:03:43.238
They've got nothing.

01:03:43.320 --> 01:03:46.370
If anything, this is just further proof
that they took the money and ran.

01:03:46.448 --> 01:03:47.618
Oh, fuck.

01:03:48.617 --> 01:03:51.867
We've got two more days
before the second shipment comes through.

01:03:51.953 --> 01:03:55.673
And we have come too far
to let a second-page story get in our way.

01:04:03.382 --> 01:04:07.012
Well, thank you for finally
coming in here, Bill. Appreciate it.

01:04:07.093 --> 01:04:09.683
When you told me about the dogs,
I knew something wasn't right.

01:04:10.597 --> 01:04:13.677
So, why'd it take you so long
to file a report?

01:04:15.602 --> 01:04:17.232
It's complicated.
[chuckles]

01:04:18.146 --> 01:04:21.066
My mother turned my own daughter
against me...

01:04:22.901 --> 01:04:24.031
[sighs]

01:04:25.319 --> 01:04:26.859
What did the cops say?

01:04:28.698 --> 01:04:32.118
They told me they would get back to me
if anything turned up.

01:04:32.201 --> 01:04:33.951
Wish I could say I was surprised.

01:04:35.163 --> 01:04:38.713
